<title type="html"><![CDATA[MMC5 question: What format do I use for raw PCM?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4089&amp;p=33221#p33221"><![CDATA[
I don't think MMC5 has any automatic way of feeding samples to its builtin raw PCM channel.  There's also no real advantage of using MMC5 PCM over the NES's builtin PCM channel.  You'd need to rewrite the code for the NSF to use cycle-timed code to feed data to the PCM output at the correct rate, like Battletoads or Skate or Die 2.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Sat May 03, 2008 10:15 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
